    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>While SARS-CoV-2 serologic testing is used to measure cumulative incidence of COVID-19, appropriate signal-to-cut off (S/Co) thresholds remain unclear. We demonstrate S/Co thresholds based on known negative samples significantly increases seropositivity and more accurately estimates cumulative incidence of disease compared to manufacturer-based thresholds.</jats:p>",
